git config --global user.name "Arora, Sachin"
git config --global user.email "sacharora99@gmail.com"
git config --list

git help
git help add

Initialize Direcory as GIT
git init

git status
git add .
git add SampleDoc.txt
git commit -m "First Git Commit"

git log
git log --author="Sachin"


Working Dir >>>> Staging Area >>>> Repository
git status   >>   git add     >>    git commit



git diff >
Difference between a.txt(Local Repo) and b.txt(Modified inside Working Area NOT NEW FILE)

git diff --staged
Difference between a.txt(Local Repo) and b.txt(Staging Area)


Delete File in Git 
git rm filename.txt


git init
git remote add origin "https://github.com/JavaShopee/git_github.git"
git pull origin master
git push origin master


Git Branching >> Creating new branch means adding just a pointer without taking extra space. In this way branching is much faster

git branch develop
git checkout deveop


git checkout master >> Move to the Target
git merge develop >> the Source


Move the file from Staging Area to Working Area
git reset HEAD filename

Move the file from local Repo to Working Area
git reset HEAD~



